Hello Noaman,
&nbsp;
Good day!

Upon checking the reason for the Rest API registration failure, we could see that the app is subscribed in your store for the $19 Starter plan that support integration of only two carrier accounts. Currently, there is already a FedEx account and an Aramex account integrated in the app and due to this the new registration was failing.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Considering the requirement, we have provided an additional account integration option for the existing plan for your store. Once done, we were able to successfully add the FedEx account through Rest API.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Once added, we have updated the carrier settings in the same way as it was in the old account. One feature "Add Buffer Days to Estimated Delivery(upto 10 days)" which you are using in the old account is currently not available in the new Rest API account. No need to worry, we have informed this to our team to enable this feature for your store and we will keep you posted on the updates once completed.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
To check the working of the new account registration, i have added a product to the cart and checked the rates for a US address and the rates from the new account integration are shown at the checkout. Please check from your end once and confirm.
&nbsp;

&nbsp;
Best regards,
Sagar K S
